==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infectious disease
<hw>In*fec"tious dis*ease"</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any disease caused by
the entrance, growth, and multiplication of microorganisms in the body;
a germ disease. It may not be contagious.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Sometimes, as distinguished from <contr>contagious disease</contr>,
such a disease communicated by germs carried in the air or water, and
thus spread without contact with the patient, as measles.</def><--
distinction still recognized? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infectiously</ent>⟦br⟧
